answers.body_markdown:
problem is with:

    for(int i = 0; i &lt; 3; ++i){
        matrix.add(i,array);
    }

`array` is instantiated at the start with `ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt; array = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();` and never get instantiated  again. That means `array` always refer to the same object. So, there is always the only copy!

Instead, try:

    for(int i = 0; i &lt; 3; ++i){
            matrix.add(i, new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(array));
    }

